task.summary: Updates to controller and model for basic database setup.
Added files not initially in project.
Homepage now shows title and content of all events stored in database
Events are given their own page and linked from the homepage.
new events can be added through website
events can be edited through website
events can be deleted through website
files added to allow for creation of users
Added/amended files so that users can register/login/logout
user is redirected to register page if not already logged in
Register page and login page are combined.
CSS changes to make it look a bit better.
Incorrect login credentials now redirect to correct page. CSS updates.
parameter checking simplified for new events
username must now be an email address (as required in the requirements document)
Default account added: admin@admin.com, password. You need to rebuild the database first using rake db:migrate, then rake db:reset db:migrate
If a user already has tickets to an event, it will not show up in featured events
Added Feature Events to nav bar Number of tickets now shown on events
Fully booked events no longer show up in Featured Events.
Past events no longer show up in Featured Events.
Avatar uploading implemented at registration form.
Moved avatar position. Added settings page and link to nav bar. CSS updates.
Uploaded avatars are now cropped and resized.
Featured events now sorted by date.
Email now shown next to avatar when signed in.
Database migrated to postgresql. You must install pg first.
README updates for reaching the site on heroku
